      "summary_zh_tw": "先不要追求很多新句子，先把幾個最常用的句型切熟。",
      "expected_output_zh_tw": "能把同一句切成 `합니다체`、`해요체`、`야/이야` 三種版本。",
      "payload": {
        "lesson_support_module": {
          "module_id": "CT-KO-BEG-001",
          "title_i18n": {
            "zh_tw": "先抓三種說話口氣",
            "en": "Start by feeling these three speech styles"
          },
          "why_here_i18n": {
            "zh_tw": "這裡先不要分析太細，你先用耳朵抓感覺就好。有些句子聽起來比較日常，有些一聽就像在跟熟朋友講。後面 G1 再把同一句拆開練。",
            "en": "You do not need to memorize rules first. Just remember one thing: sentence endings change depending on who you are speaking to. Start with the three most common styles, and when unsure, use `~아요/어요/해요`."
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "target": "很正式時這樣講：`~습니다 / ~ㅂ니다`",
              "explain_i18n": {
                "zh_tw": "像發表、公告、面試，或你想把語氣拉高一點時會用。",
                "en": "Use this in presentations, notices, interviews, or when you want to sound more formal."
              }
            },
            {
              "target": "平常先這樣講：`~아요 / ~어요 / ~해요`",
              "explain_i18n": {
                "zh_tw": "這個最常用，也最安全。第一次見面、旅行、問路、買東西先用這個通常不會錯。",
                "en": "This is the most common and safest choice for everyday situations."
              }
            },
            {
              "target": "熟了再這樣講：`~야 / ~이야`",
              "explain_i18n": {
                "zh_tw": "這是跟熟朋友講話時常用的說法。還不熟的時候，先不要急著切過去。",
                "en": "This is commonly used with close friends. Do not rush into it when you are not close yet."
              }
            }
          ]
